Invitations were forwarded to 558 national and international endoscopists. A maximum of two reminders were sent with an interval of 2 weeks after the first invitation. Between November 15, 2021 and December 31, 2021, 140 participants responded to the survey (response rate 25.0%) (
Table 1
). Of these, 124 (88.6%) completed the survey, 64.5% of them being male with a mean age of 46.5 years with three-quarters working in the Netherlands (75.8%). The participants included consultant gastroenterologists (79.8%), resident gastroenterologists (15.3%), nurse endoscopists (2.4%), and one surgical endoscopist (0.8%). Most of the respondents worked at a non-academic teaching hospital (42.7%) and 37.1% at an academic hospital. Almost 50% of participants performed more than 50 EMRs or ESDs yearly and 56.5% considered themselves an EMR expert (
Table 1
).
